lpha$ and [SII] surface brightnesses show a good correlation\nwith the X-ray luminosity of the SNR candidates that are center-bright. The SNR\ncandidates with X-ray counterparts have higher surface brightnesses in\nH$\\alpha$ and [SII] and smaller sizes than those without such counterparts.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 18 Mar 2014 04:04:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-19"}
